NAME
    readlink - print resolved symbolic links

SYNOPSIS
    readlink [options] <file...>

DESCRIPTION
    Prints the target of a symbolic link. With -f, prints the
    canonical absolute pathname.

OPTIONS
    -f              Canonicalize path (resolve all symlinks)
    -e              Like -f, but path must exist
    -m              Like -f, but path need not exist
    -n              No trailing newline
    -q              Quiet (suppress error messages)
    -v              Verbose

EXAMPLES
    readlink /link
        /path/to/target

    readlink -f /link
        /absolute/path/to/target

    readlink -e /link
        Error if target doesn't exist

    readlink -n link1 link2
        Output without newlines

EXIT STATUS
    0       Success
    1       Error or not a symbolic link

SEE ALSO
    realpath, ln, stat
